        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 29 at 7:30PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 730 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles southeast of Beaver, moving north at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Beaver.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
